A Stream is not a data structure and doesnt hold the data. It represent a pipeline through which data will flow and which functions to operate on the data. Especially you cannot point to a location in the stream where a certain element exists. What you could do is stream over the indices, filter out the index which you don&#39;t need and map to the list elements:

    int n = 3;
    List&lt;Integer&gt; myList = List.of(1, 2, 3, 4, 5);
    IntStream.range(0, myList.size())
             .filter(i -&gt; i !=n)
             .map(myList::get)
             .forEach(System.out::println);

or include only elements you need from the source when streaming:

    Stream.concat(myList.subList(0, n).stream(), myList.subList(n+1, myList.size()).stream())
              .forEach(System.out::println);

