Neo4j Java driver connects to servers. Servers can have default databases per users.

`:use` as in the Neo4j Browser (or Cypher-Shell) is not a Cypher-Command. It&#39;s a browser respectively Cypher-Shell command, telling the corresponding tool to switch this session to another database on the server.

The pendant to this on the Java-Driver is the `SessionConfig` class and this builder method [`public static SessionConfig forDatabase(String database)`][1]. In code:

```java
